# Agent tool skill caches, generated skill dirs, and skills lockfile.
# These appear as untracked when AI agents (Cursor, Claude, etc.) materialize
# skills such as lark-im into the cwd for the current project.
# The lark-im (Feishu/Lark IM via larksuite/cli) was the source of the
# "lark skill increment" visible in git status for this fork workspace.
# .claude/ is already ignored; extend the pattern to other tools' caches.
# Also ignore the pi skills-lock.json when it only records internal skills.
.agent/
.agents/
.coco/
.kiro/
.qwen/
.trae/
.trae-cn/
.pi/skills/lark-im
skills-lock.json
